        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 15 at 6:22AM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>Patches of dense fog have developed across parts of the northern
foothills and northwest Piedmont of North Carolina early this
morning. The visibility has been reduced to one-half mile or less
in some spots, particularly low-lying areas and around bodies of
water. The fog should dissipate by mid-morning.

If driving across the area, be on the lookout for sharply reduced
visibility. Slow down and use your low-beam headlights.
</description>
